                            <comment id="12650108" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 04:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There already seems to be a count of store files in the region server metrics. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/help_16.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch that adds a metric for store file indexes size in MB. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650282" author="stack" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 19:08:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My only reservation is that this is an expensive test to do every ten seconds.  We&apos;ll be going to the filesystem for every store file on the regionserver to find its size.  Looking at code, in hdfs, this involves a trip to the namenode by my reading.  So, every ten seconds, all nodes will ask the namenode about all store files.   Do we want to add this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650283" author="stack" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 19:09:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could we cache this info in HbaseMapFile somewhere on open and use that in metrics?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650293" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 19:40:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The information can just be cached in HStoreFile. Updated patch attached. Patch should apply with fuzz. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650298" author="stack" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 19:55:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.  Maybe make public long indexLength() throws IOException { synchronized when you commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650325" author="stack" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 21:07:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, this issue was about adding a count of stores to metrics.  There is already a count of storefiles and of memory help up in store memcaches, but I was thinking that a count of stores themselves would also be useful?  I was thinking of the streamy case where there are a couple of tables each with different counts of stores.  Dependent on the regions an HRS gets loaded with, it can have a various number of Stores.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650328" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 21:16:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated description. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650329" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 21:17:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650331" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 21:21:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, missed stack&apos;s last comment. Will add the metric as requested.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12650341" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 21:49:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed additional metric for store count.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
